
'''= Polish mutual aid practice in the countryside'''


=Description=

Wojtek Mejor:

"There is this thing called TŁOKA (pronunc.: TUOKA) in Poland which is:

"...a slavic custom of collective, unpaid help in the rural areas. It survived until the second half of the 20th century. . . . The work began and ended with a treat (food and often music and dancing) . . . The church allowed it even on Sundays. . . ."


